text":"For this man was counted worthy of more glory than Moses, inasmuch as he who hath builded the house hath more honour than the house.","year":64},{"id":"recBPDyidHicyewqg","ref":"Heb.3.4","text":"For every house is builded by some man; but he that built all things is God.","year":64},{"id":"recUF2FQJdtJZ0Sqk","ref":"Heb.3.5","text":"And Moses verily was faithful in all his house, as a servant, for a testimony of those things which were to be spoken after;","year":64},{"id":"recQkDfhy9Oznwx47","ref":"Heb.3.6","text":"But Christ as a son over his own house; whose house are we, if we hold fast the confidence and the rejoicing of the hope firm unto the end.","year":64},{"id":"rec9RwmRuDEnB05Fa","ref":"Heb.3.7","text":"Wherefore (as the Holy Ghost saith, To day if ye will hear his voice,","year":64},{"id":"recdmtcXFB9dX0K0K","ref":"Heb.3.8","text":"Harden not your hearts, as in the provocation, in the day of temptation in the wilderness:","year":64}]}
